Ford Assistant, Multi-Day Scheduling; more feature enhancements

We’ve got updates on updates. 

For the updates that need your vehicle to be turned off for a short while, that’s where our new Multi-Day Scheduling comes in. We know you’re busy, so this feature will allow you to schedule and stagger your updates for the days and times that work best for you. Our latest Update Now function lets you install an update as soon as it’s ready for your vehicle, instead of having to wait for your scheduled time. This will help you get the updates faster and allow you a lot more flexibility.

Ever wanted to talk to your vehicle? Well, now you can with your own Ford Assistant. Just say, “OK, Ford” to wake up your assistant and ask questions like “How does my cruise control work?” or “When does my warranty expire?”.

Taking the place of Intelligent Adaptive Cruise Control, Speed Sign Recognition has been added to the SYNC® Driver Assistance menu. You can now find it on your in-vehicle screen under Adaptive Cruise Control.

If you ever want to stimulate your mind while parked, we’ve added a couple of puzzle games called Blocks & Tiles, which can be found on your in-vehicle screen. The Tiles puzzle will challenge you to match colors and shapes, while the goal of Blocks is to match shaped blocks. 

So yeah, there’s a lot of cool stuff going on. 

Ongoing updates like this help you enjoy the best possible version of your Mustang Mach-E vehicle. Keep in mind that feature availability varies by model. For more information on these features, visit owner.ford.com or your digital Owner’s Manual.
